    postGame:
      "# üßä THE ICE BOWL BLOODBATH! üßä\n\nHoly frozen toes, sports fans! What a match! What a massacre! If you missed this one, you missed a masterclass in defensive brutality! We saw limbs flying, weapons swinging, and bodies hitting the permafrost with a sound like cracking thunder! It wasn't a high-scoring affair, but who needs points when you have PAIN? That's what I always say!\n\nThe action started fast and frantic in the freezing rain. Both teams came out of the gate looking to make a statement, but the defenses were tighter than a miser's purse strings! We saw missed tackle after missed tackle as the players slid around on the icy field. It looked like a dance recital gone wrong out there for a minute!\n\nThe Zmeigorod Snessengers thought they had an opening when the Yetis' **Jessy Debbie** tried to throw a long bomb. But **Rose Kluge**‚Äîoh, sweet Rose!‚Äîread it like a cheap dime novel and snatched that ball out of the air! INTERCEPTION! The swamp-folk were in business! Or so they thought.\n\nThe Snessengers' offense, however, seemed to be suffering from a severe case of frostbite. **Kleinstein MacGregor** lined up for a shot from Home Field‚Äîa gimme for a pro!‚Äîand shanked it wide! Completely missed the goal! I tell you, folks, you could see the disappointment on Valos's face all the way from the bog!\n\nThen, the Yetis decided that if they couldn't score points, they would score fractures! The violence cranked up to eleven! **Selima Si**, wearing those garish undergarments for luck, lowered the boom on **Alded Sanjay**. CRUNCH! Sanjay went down like a sack of potatoes and didn't get up! That is an INJURY, folks! That is the sound of victory!\n\nBut the Yetis weren't done! Not by a long shot! Moments later, **Hilaire Guevara** caught **Avaria Revell** with a tackle that would have stopped a charging rhino. BAM! Another Snessenger bites the ice! Two players down! The Grove's roster is getting thinner by the minute! I haven't seen that much carnage since the last time I visited the Demon Prison cafeteria!\n\nDespite the Yetis turning the Snessengers into a field hospital, nobody could find the net! **Duky Orelee** missed a shot! **Sayers Erdda** missed a shot! It was a comedy of errors, if comedy involved heavy weaponry and concussions. The regulation whistle blew with a score of absolute ZERO to absolute ZERO.\n\nWe went to **OVERTIME**! Sudden death! The tension was palpable! The crowd at the Palisade was going wild, or maybe they were just trying to keep warm! The ball was live, and **Isborne Krause** scooped it up. It was anyone's game!\n\nBut then, like a bolt of lightning in a blizzard, **Sale Tocci** took control! She grabbed that leather troll head, weaved through the exhausted, battered, and bruised Snessengers defense, and charged into the End Zone! With a scream that echoed across the tundra, she **DUNKED THE BALL INTO THE GOAL!**\n\nGAME OVER! The South Pole Yetis take it home! A hard-fought, bloody, freezing victory for the locals! The Snessengers are going to have a long, painful limp back to Zmeigorod to explain this one to Oona. Maybe next time, bring fewer raw eggs and more bandages!\n\n**FINAL SCORE:**\n**The South Pole Yetis: 1**\n**The Zmeigorod Snessengers: 0**\n\nThis is Nok the Corrupter, reminding you to ice your bruises and sharpen your axes! Goodnight, Osterra!",
