      "## üí• POST-GAME REPORT: LIGHTS OUT FOR OAK!\n\nWell, folks, put a cork in the bottle and wipe the blood off the seats, because this one is in the history books! The final whistle has blown at Fletchings Field, and unfortunately, the forces of unbearable brightness have prevailed. **The Haven Lights take it down with a final score of 4 to 2 over Oak & Onslaught.** It disgusts me to say it, but the Lights flickered to life just enough to steal the win.\n\nThe game started with the coordination of a headless chicken convention. We saw dropped passes, missed tackles, and wild shots flying everywhere! Zwart Bunns tried to shoot early for Haven but couldn't hit the broad side of a barn, and Ema Ulrick returned the favor for Oak by launching the ball into the stratosphere. It was looking like a scoreless bore until the violence finally kicked in!\n\nAnd oh, did it kick in! Affra Yanaton, bless their violent heart, decided enough was enough. They lined up Marlane Lounge and delivered a tackle so hard I felt it in my molars! ü¶¥ CRACK! Lounge went down, INJURED, and was dragged off the field. That is the kind of initiative I like to see! If you can't score, just break the opponent's bones!\n\nBut, credit where it's due‚Äîeven if I hate giving it‚ÄîMarlane Lounge came back from the dead thanks to Healer Riffle Harrington. And Marlane didn't just come back; they came back angry. Moments after returning, Lounge plowed into Millham Evangeline, sending the Bardiche-wielder straight to the dirt with a nasty injury! Revenge is a dish best served with a side of concussion, folks!\n\nWe went into Halftime with a 0-0 deadlock, mostly because nobody could hold onto the slippery leather. I assume the players spent the break crying to their mothers or, in Haven's case, singing campfire songs. Whatever they did, it woke them up for the second half.\n\nOut of the gate, Shiroma Salim finally remembered the point of the game. He launched a shot from Home Field‚Äîa risky move!‚Äîand drilled it right through the goal! **2-0 Haven Lights!** Silence fell over the Warden fans, probably because they were too busy admiring the trees to cheer.\n\nBut Oak & Onslaught wasn't done yet! Milt Casady, the man who loves a good chant, picked up the ball in Center Field. He shook off a tackle and fired a rocket to tie the game! **2-2!** We had ourselves a real scrap, folks! The crowd went wild, or at least as wild as people associated with Sir Falric can get without charging a fee.\n\nThen came the late-game butchery! Symer Crissy of Oak & Onslaught absolutely leveled Riffle Heyde, taking them out of the game completely! INJURY! And moments later, Normi Glaudia smashed Farand Keil into the turf! Another INJURY! Oak was winning the physical war, racking up the body count like true champions of chaos!\n\nHowever, tragedy struck for the home team. Despite the pile of broken Haven bodies, that pesky Marlane Lounge‚Äîthe one who had already been injured once today!‚Äîfound the ball in their hands again. From Home Field, Lounge launched a Hail Mary shot... and **SCORES! 4-2 Haven!** Unbelievable!\n\nMilt Casady tried desperately to answer back in the dying seconds, but his final shot went wide, much like Sir Randy's fashion sense. The clock hit zero, and the Haven Lights celebrated their unholy victory. A sad day for darkness, but a great day for orthopedic surgeons! Until next week, this is Nok the Corrupter signing off‚Äîremember, if you can't win, make sure the other guy can't walk!",
