    postGame:
      "# üç∫ THE HANGOVER REPORT: YETIS FREEZE OUT THE PRIVATEERS! üç∫\n\n**WHAT A NIGHT! WHAT A FIGHT! WHAT A DISGRACE TO SOBRIETY!** \n\nFolks, I haven't seen this much stumbling since **High Venture Brennen Farno** tried to explain inflation to the poor! The final score is in, and the **South Pole Yetis** have stumbled their way to victory over the **Tortell Privateers**, **4 to 2**! The sun was hot, the drinks were cold, and the blood was lukewarm! Let's crack open the recap of this intoxicating display of violence!\n\nThe game started with the coordination of a three-legged dog race. We saw block after block as the alcohol hadn't quite hit the bloodstream yet. Both teams were testing the waters, or should I say, the liquor! The silence was broken when the Yetis' **Hilaire Guevara** decided that **Lilithe Royce** needed a nap, delivering a bone-crunching tackle that sent the Privateer off on a stretcher! But don't worry, **Eugen Zacks** slapped a helmet on her head and sent her back in‚Äîmedicinal brandy works wonders, folks!\n\nThe Privateers struck first blood on the scoreboard, though! **Loralee Sunny**, looking surprisingly steady on her feet, weaved through the defense and **DUNKED** that troll head right into the End Zone! **1-0 Privateers!** The crowd went wild, and by wild, I mean they started chugging Imra's special reserve like it was water! The intoxicating mist of victory‚Äîand spirits‚Äîdescended upon the field.\n\nThen came **HALFTIME**, or as I like to call it, \"Happy Hour!\" Both teams retreated to their benches, not for rest, but to heed the call of the Open Bar. When they came back out, oh boy, the physics engine of reality took a vacation. Players were swaying like trees in a hurricane! \n\nThe second half belonged to the Yetis, and specifically to their shooters! But first, **Lilithe Royce**, clearly fueled by a vengeance cocktail, went on a rampage! She tipsily tackled **Selima Si** into oblivion, and moments later, flattened **Sayers Erdda**! She was a drunken wrecking ball, proving that aiming juice really does improve your aggression!\n\nHowever, you can't tackle a ball that's flying over your head! **Duky Orelee**, clapping a prime number of times‚Äîwhich I assume is harder when you're seeing double‚Äîlaunched a beauty from Center Field! **BOOM!** Two points for the Yetis! The score flipped to **2-1**, and the South Pole bench erupted in a chorus of slurred cheering and belching!\n\nThe violence didn't stop there. **Kidder Starkey** of the Privateers decided to join the party, smashing **Jessy Debbie** into the turf. But the Yetis kept their eyes on the prize, or at least one of their four eyes did. **Isborne Krause**, miraculously staying upright despite the open bar, launched another rocket from Home Field! **ANOTHER TWO POINTER!** The Yetis extended their lead to **4-1**!\n\nThe Privateers tried to rally late in the game. **Melisande Eustacia**, stumbling around like **King Nezmear** after a werewolf breeding mishap, managed to crash into the End Zone for a pity dunk. It brought the score to **4-2**, but it was too little, too late‚Äîand definitely too drunk.\n\nThe clock ticked down, bodies were strewn across the pristine resort grass like garnish in a bloody mary, and the **South Pole Yetis** claimed victory! A massive win for the visitors, who proved that they can hold their liquor just as well as they hold a grudge. \n\nAs for the **Tortell Privateers**, maybe **Elspeth Ortell** needs to spike the punch a little less next time, or perhaps **Imra** needs to invent a potion that prevents double vision! Until next week, this is **Nok the Corrupter**, signing off and reminding you: **IF YOU CAN'T BEAT 'EM, EAT 'EM!** (Or at least drink them under the table!)",
